            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/news-wrap-government-to-drop-tax-claims-and-audits-of-trump</link>
            <description><![CDATA[In our news wrap Tuesday, acting Attorney General Todd Blanche said the government will drop any tax claims and audits of President Trump, Blanche also defended the creation of a nearly $1.8 billion 'anti-weaponization' fund and President Trump endorsed Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton in next week's Senate runoff, rather than the Republican incumbent John Cornyn.]]></description>
